# GAB Library (.lib) Files

You are editing a **GAB library** -- a reusable collection of subroutines included by `.g2u` scripts via `Program.Sub.IncludeFile`.

## Key Differences from .g2u
- No `ScreenSU` sub (libraries have no GUI declarations)
- No `Main` entry point -- libraries provide subs called by the including script
- Same encoding: **UTF-8 with BOM**, **CRLF**, no trailing newline
- Same signing: requires a companion `.sig` file

## Include Convention
Scripts include libraries with: `Program.Sub.IncludeFile("libraryname.lib")`
The runtime resolves `.lib` files relative to the script's directory, then falls back to `<GlobalDirectory>\PLUGINS\gab` (see `AGENTS.PROJECT.md` for the Global Directory path).

## Standard Libraries
Numbered `.lib` files in `<GlobalDirectory>\PLUGINS\gab` (e.g. `1000.lib`, `175100.lib`) are GS Mobile shared libraries. Each has a companion `*Validate.lib` for input validation.

## Golden Rule
Same as .g2u: **never invent APIs**. Verify via `gab_api_lookup` MCP tool. No inline math operators or `+` string concat.

## Routing
Load `agents/AGENTS.GAB.md` for the full reference.
